# GIT WORKFLOW RULES

> Clean history = understandable history. Consistent commits = easy review.

---

## BRANCH STRATEGY (Size A)

```
main (production)
├── development (staging/development)
│   ├── feature/xxx
│   ├── bugfix/xxx
│   └── refactor/xxx
└── hotfix/xxx
```

---

## BRANCH NAMING

```
<type>/<short-description>
```

| Type | When | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| `feature/` | New functionality | `feature/add-cart` |
| `bugfix/` | Bug fix | `bugfix/fix-login-error` |
| `hotfix/` | Critical production fix | `hotfix/critical-payment-fix` |
| `refactor/` | Refactoring | `refactor/auth-module` |
| `chore/` | Infrastructure, deps | `chore/update-deps` |

---

## CONVENTIONAL COMMITS

```
<type>(<scope?>): <subject>
```

| Type | When | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature | `feat(cart): add quantity selector` |
| `fix` | Bug fix | `fix(auth): handle expired token` |
| `docs` | Documentation | `docs: update API docs` |
| `refactor` | Refactoring | `refactor(api): extract validation` |
| `perf` | Performance | `perf(images): implement lazy loading` |
| `chore` | Maintenance | `chore: update dependencies` |

---

## RULES

- Feature branches → squash merge
- Hotfix → merge commit
- PRs ≤ 400 lines (ideally ≤ 200)
- ❌ Never force push to main/development
- ❌ Never commit secrets or `.env` files
- ✅ Always `git diff --staged` before commit

